From c065250f0833f710e11a11cd565d38c6277d3c23 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shreedhar Parande <sparande@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Sep 2025 15:08:09 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD:KW: Remove redundant check for
 mld_link_id

Remove the redundant sanity check for mld_link_id and
data from get_link_sta_inactive_time(), as the caller
already performs these validations.

Patch-dependency: r69-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-driver-Add-support-for-MLD-max-idle-period.patch
Patch-work: None
Fixes: I229c2e2663c ('UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD:Add MLO support for MLD BSS Max Idle Period')

Signed-off-by: Shreedhar Parande <sparande@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c b/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c
index e25b504..ac0515a 100644
--- a/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c
+++ b/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c
@@ -8302,7 +8302,7 @@ static int get_link_sta_inactive_time(struct hostap_sta_driver_data *data,
 				      struct nlattr *link_sta_stats[],
 				      u8 mld_link_id)
 {
-	if (!data || !link_sta_stats || (mld_link_id > MAX_NUM_MLD_LINKS))
+	if (!link_sta_stats)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	if (!link_sta_stats[NL80211_STA_INFO_INACTIVE_TIME])
-- 
2.34.1

